- check the list of connected deviced to your computer 

1.$lsblk - check the list of connected deviced to your computer 

2. Create a directory for the flash drive.
2.1 Best pracite is in the /mnt directory.
$sudo mkdir /mnt/usb-backup

3. Mount the removable device to the /mnt/usb-backup directory
$sudo mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt/usb-backup

4. May need to install ntfs-3g so the system can read the ntfs file system type
$sudo pacman -S ntfs-3g

---------------------------------
4. Unmount 

$sudo unmount
